    <fr:title text="Linear MDP">Linear MDP</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
An MDP <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {M}=(\mathcal {S},\mathcal {A},H,P,r)]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:em>linear MDP</html:em> if there exists two feature maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi :\mathcal {S}\times \mathcal {A}\rightarrow \mathbb {R}^{d}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu :\mathcal {S}\rightarrow \mathbb {R}^{d}]]></fr:tex> and a vector <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\theta _{r}\in \mathbb {R}^{d}]]></fr:tex>, such that

<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[P(s^{\prime }|s,a)=\langle \phi (s,a),\mu (s^{\prime })\rangle ,\quad  r(s,a)=\langle \phi (s,a),\theta _{r}\rangle ]]></fr:tex>

and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> also satisfy the normalization conditions:

<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
\begin {align*}
  &\forall (s,a),\ \lVert  \phi (s,a) \rVert _{2} \leq  1,\ \lVert  \theta _{r}\rVert _{2} \leq  \sqrt {d} \\
  &\forall  g:\mathcal {S}\rightarrow \mathbb {R},\ \lVert  g \rVert _{L_{\infty }}\leq  1\ \Rightarrow \left \lVert  \int _{\mathcal {S}}\mu (s^{\prime })g(s^{\prime })ds^{\prime }\right  \rVert _{2}\leq  \sqrt {d}
\end {align*}
]]></fr:tex></html:p>
